It seems the image_editing skill doesn't have explicit commands listed. However, I can use standard Linux tools to convert images to grayscale. I'll use the `convert` command from ImageMagick to achieve this.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The image_editing skill directory doesn't show specific commands. However, I can use the 'convert' command from ImageMagick to convert images to grayscale. This is a standard Linux tool that should be available.",
  "plan": "I'll use a loop to convert each keyframe PNG file to grayscale using ImageMagick's 'convert' command. The command will be run in-place, overwriting the original files.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "for file in /root/keyframes_*.png; do convert \"$file\" -colorspace Gray \"$file\"; done\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ]
}
```
